
[1]alkahest

   AL'KAHEST, n.

   A universal dissolvent; a menstrumm capable of dissolving every body,
   which Paracelsus and Van Helmont pretended they possessed. This
   pretense no longer imposses on the credulity of any man.

   The word is sometimes used for fixed salts volatilized.
